column5: I love walking this section of the river as I know theres always a chance to see some wild life.  As I hit one wooded section,I see the sign. The white flag sign of a deer hopping off. Hmm,maybe I,ll see more. So I start to walk slower and sure enough I see one on the hill.  Healthy doe.     River looked inviting today. I decided to give the bead a work out. Fishing has been tough.  I finally got my first steel on a bead. Not huge but a first. Sorry about the mud. It was a quick land,shot and release.    Weatherman has been on my side for getting out. Lets hope the next 4 days are the same.
Nice pics Brian, have enjoyed your pics and video's through the year, keep up the good work
Nice couple of doe's there . Lots of fluorescent orange on the field edges this am and yesterday, lots of shots also. Nice healthy fish, love the bead. Ry

looks like a good day out
